item.title: Difference between scones and biscuits
item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: Are scones and biscuits the same thing?Following etiquette, the correct pronunciation of scone is ‘skon’, to rhyme with ‘gone’, rather than ‘skone’ to rhyme with ‘bone’. The ‘posh’ pronunciation of scone really isn’t so posh after all.Are English scones the same as American biscuits?Scones and biscuits are different things in the USA. We call scones “scones”, just like the British do. Most Americans know the difference between the two. A biscuit (in the USA) is a savory quick bread that is usually round and is served buttered with a meal, or sometimes with gravy.

item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: Yannick Carrasco is a professional football player from Belgium who presently plays as a winger for Atlético Madrid. After joining Monaco in 2012, Carrasco rapidly made a name for himself as a gifted young player. He spent his three years at the club helping Monaco win the Ligue 2 title in 2012–2013 and gain promotion to the Ligue 1 league. During his final season in Monaco, Carrasco was an important part of the team that played in the UEFA Champions League.
